   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Ridge Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "0c02d353",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Ridge Regression is a regularized version of linear regression that adds a penalty term to the \n",
    "loss function to prevent overfitting — especially useful when features are highly correlated (multicollinearity)\n",
    "\n",
    "Key Idea:\n",
    "\n",
    "It minimizes:\n",
    "MSE + λ * Σ(coefficient²) = (1/n) * Σ(yᵢ - ŷᵢ)² + λ * Σ(coefficient²)\n",
    "→ The λ (lambda) controls how much we penalize large coefficients."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f047ec90",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Why it helps:\n",
    "-Shrinks coefficients toward zero (but never to zero) → reduces model complexity.\n",
    "-Stabilizes estimates when features are correlated.\n",
    "-Improves generalization on unseen data.\n",
    "\n",
    "Think of it as: “Don’t let any one feature dominate — keep all coefficients small.”\n",
    "\n",
    "When to use:\n",
    "Many correlated features\n",
    "High-dimensional data   \n",
    "Linear models prone to overfitting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a3dc42d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Lasso Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c0923c37",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Lasso Regression is a regularized version of linear regression that adds a penalty term to the loss function to prevent overfitting — especially useful when you want automatic feature selection by eliminating irrelevant features.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key Idea:\n",
    "It minimizes: \n",
    "MSE + λ * Σ(|coefficient|) = (1/n) * Σ(yᵢ - ŷᵢ)² + λ * Σ(|coefficient|) \n",
    "→ The λ (lambda) controls how much we penalize large coefficients."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5456efb9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Why it helps:\n",
    "-Shrinks coefficients toward zero and sets some exactly to zero → automatic feature selection.\n",
    "-Removes irrelevant features from the model entirely.\n",
    "-Improves model interpretability by identifying only important predictors.\n",
    "-Improves generalization on unseen data.\n",
    "\n",
    "Think of it as: \"Keep only the most important features — eliminate the rest.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "When to use:\n",
    "-Many features, but only some are relevant\n",
    "-High-dimensional data with suspected irrelevant predictors\n",
    "-Need interpretable models with fewer features\n",
    "-Want automatic feature selection built into the model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "110bdf2a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Lasso vs Ridge:\n",
    "Lasso: Coefficients → zero (feature elimination)\n",
    "Ridge: Coefficients → small but non-zero (keeps all features)"
   ]
  }
 ],
